# 🧭 Overview

This machine initially appeared to revolve around an exposed SSH private key hidden inside a backup directory.

After spending some time attempting to crack and use the key, it became clear that the real attack path was elsewhere.

The breakthrough came from investigating the CGI directory and identifying a classic Shellshock vulnerability which ultimately provided remote code execution.

From there, kernel enumeration revealed a viable privilege escalation path leading to root.

